The paper deals with the problem of dictionary learning and sparse coding, which are fundamental topics in machine learning and computer vision. The use of neural architectures and the focus on scalability suggest that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category. However, the paper also discusses applications in computer vision (cs.CV), and the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and optimization techniques (cs.IT) further support this. Finally, the mention of "Neurally plausible" suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
